@c    THE FIRST BOOK OF PARALIPOMENON



@c    These Books are called by the Greek interpreters, Paralipomenon, that
@c    is, of things left out, or omitted; because they are a kind of a
@c    supplement of such things as were passed over in the books of the
@c    Kings.  The Hebrews call them Dibre Haijamim, that is, The words of the
@c    days, or The Chronicles.--Not that they are the books which are so
@c    often quoted in the Kings, under the title of the words of the days of
@c    the kings of Israel, and of the kings of Juda:  for the books of
@c    Paralipomenon were written after the books of Kings:  but because in all
@c    probability they have been abridged from those ancient words of the
@c    days, by Esdras or some other sacred writer.



