@c    1:52. Duke Oolibama, duke Ela, duke Phinon,

@c    1:53. Duke Cenez, duke Theman, duke Mabsar,

@c    1:54. Duke Magdiel, duke Hiram.  These are the dukes of Edom.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 2


@c    The twelve tribes of Israel.  The genealogy of Juda down to David.  Other
@c    genealogies of the tribe of Juda.

@c    2:1. And these are the sons of Israel:  Ruben, Simeon, Levi, Juda,
@c    Issachar, and Zabulon,

@c    2:2. Dan, Joseph, Benjamin, Nephtali, Gad, and Aser.

@c    2:3. The sons of Juda:  Her, Onan and Sela.  These three were born to him
@c    of the Chanaanitess the daughter of Sue.  And Her the firstborn of Juda,
@c    was wicked in the sight of the Lord, and he slew him.

@c    2:4. And Thamar his daughter in law bore him Phares and Zara.  So all
@c    the sons of Juda were five.

@c    2:5. And the sons of Phares, were Hesron and Hamul.

@c    2:6. And the sons also of Zare:  Zamri, and Ethan, and Eman, and
@c    Chalchal, and Dara, five in all.

@c    2:7. And the sons of Charmi:  Achar, who troubled Israel, and sinned by
@c    the theft of the anathema.

@c    Achar. . .Alias Achan.  Jos. 7.--Ibid.  The anathema. . .The thing
@c    devoted or accursed, viz., the spoils of Jericho.

@c    2:8. The sons of Ethan:  Azarias,

@c    2:9. And the sons of Hesron that were born to him:  Jerameel, and Ram,
@c    and Calubi.

@c    2:10. And Ram begot Aminadab, and Aminadab begot Nahasson, prince of
@c    the children of Juda.

@c    Ram. . .He is commonly called Aram.  But it is to be observed here, once
@c    for all, that it was a common thing among the Hebrews for the same
@c    persons to have different names:  and that it is not impossible among so
@c    many proper names, as here occur in the first nine chapters of this
@c    book, that the transcribers of the ancient Hebrew copies may have made
@c    some slips in the orthography.

@c    2:11. And Nahasson begot Salma, the father of Booz.

@c    2:12. And Booz begot Obed, and Obed begot Isai.

@c    2:13. And Isai begot Eliab his firstborn, the second Abinadab, the
@c    third Simmaa,

@c    2:14. The fourth, Nathanael, the fifth Raddai,

@c    2:15. The sixth Asom, the seventh David.

@c    2:16. And their sisters were Sarvia, and Abigail.  The sons of Sarvia:
@c    Abisai, Joab, and Asael, three.

@c    2:17. And Abigail bore Amasa, whose father was Jether the Ismahelite.

@c    2:18. And Caleb the son of Hesron took a wife named Azuba, of whom he
@c    had Jerioth:  and her sons were Jaser, and Sobab, and Ardon.

@c    Caleb. . .Alias Calubi, ver. 9.

@c    2:19. And when Azuba was dead, Caleb took to wife Ephrata:  who bore him
@c    Hur.

@c    2:20. And Hur begot Uri:  and Uri begot Bezeleel.

@c    2:21. And afterwards Hesron went in to the daughter of Machir the
@c    father of Galaad, and took her to wife when he was threescore years
