@c    2:22. And Segub begot Jair, and he had three and twenty cities in the
@c    land of Galaad.

@c    2:23. And he took Gessur, and Aram the towns of Jair, and Canath, and
@c    the villages thereof, threescore cities.  All these, the sons of Machir
@c    father of Galaad.

@c    2:24. And when Hesron was dead, Caleb went in to Ephrata.  Hesron also
