@c    2:25. And the sons of Jerameel the firstborn of Hesron, were Ram his
@c    firstborn, and Buna, and Aram, and Asom, and Achia.

@c    2:26. And Jerameel married another wife, named Atara, who was the
@c    mother of Onam.

@c    2:27. And the sons of Ram the firstborn of Jerameel, were Moos, Jamin,
@c    and Achar.

@c    2:28. And Onam had sons Semei, and Jada.  And the sons of Semei:  Nadab,
@c    and Abisur.

@c    2:29. And the name of Abisur's wife was Abihail, who bore him Ahobban,
@c    and Molid.

@c    2:30. And the sons of Nadab were Saled and Apphaim.  And Saled died
@c    without children.

@c    2:31. But the son of Apphaim was Jesi:  and Jesi begot Sesan.  And Sesan
@c    begot Oholai.

@c    2:32. And the sons of Jada the brother of Semei:  Jether and Jonathan.
@c    And Jether also died without children.

@c    2:33. But Jonathan begot Phaleth, and Ziza.  These were the sons of
@c    Jerameel.

@c    2:34. And Sesan had no sons, but daughters and a servant an Egyptian,
@c    named Jeraa.

@c    2:35. And he gave him his daughter to wife:  and she bore him Ethei.

@c    2:36. And Ethei begot Nathan, and Nathan begot Zabad.

@c    2:37. And Zabad begot Ophlal, and Ophlal begot Obed.

@c    2:38. Obed begot Jehu, Jehu begot Azarias.

@c    2:39. Azarias begot Helles, and Helles begot Elasa.

@c    2:40. Elasa begot Sisamoi, Sisamoi begot Sellum,

@c    2:41. Sellum begot Icamia, and Icamia begot Elisama.

@c    2:42. Now the sons of Caleb the brother of Jerameel were Mesa his
@c    firstborn, who was the father of Siph:  and the sons of Maresa father of
@c    Hebron.

@c    2:43. And the sons of Hebron, Core, and Thaphua, and Recem, and Samma.

@c    2:44. And Samma begot Raham, the father of Jercaam, and Recem begot
@c    Sammai.

@c    2:45. The son of Sammai, Maon:  and Maon the father of Bethsur.

@c    2:46. And Epha the concubine of Caleb bore Haran, and Mosa, and Gezez.
@c    And Haran begot Gezez.

@c    2:47. And the sons of Jahaddai, Rogom, and Joathan, and Gesan, and
@c    Phalet, and Epha, and Saaph.

@c    2:48. And Maacha the concubine of Caleb bore Saber, and Tharana.

@c    2:49. And Saaph the father of Madmena begot Sue the father of Machbena,
@c    and the father of Gabaa.  And the daughter of Caleb was Achsa.

@c    2:50. These were the sons of Caleb, the son of Hur the firstborn of
@c    Ephrata, Sobal the father of Cariathiarim.

@c    2:51. Salma the father of Bethlehem, Hariph the father of Bethgader.

@c    2:52. And Sobal the father of Cariathiarim had sons:  he that saw half
@c    of the places of rest.

@c    He that saw, etc. . .The Latin interpreter seems to have given us here,
@c    instead of the proper names, the meaning of those names in the Hebrew.
@c    He has done in like manner, ver. 55.

@c    2:53. And of the kindred of Cariathiarim, the Jethrites, and
@c    Aphuthites, and Semathites, and Maserites.  Of them came the Saraites,
@c    and Esthaolites.

@c    2:54. The sons of Salma, Bethlehem, and Netophathi, the crowns of the
@c    house of Joab, and half of the place of rest of Sarai.

@c    2:55. And the families of the scribes that dwell in Jabes, singing and
@c    making melody, and abiding in tents.  These are the Cinites, who came of
@c    Calor (Chamath) father of the house of Rechab.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 3


@c    The genealogy of the house of David.

@c    3:1. Now these were the sons of David that were born to him in Hebron:
@c    the firstborn Amnon of Achinoam the Jezrahelitess, the second Daniel of
@c    Abigail the Carmelitess.

@c    3:2. The third Absalom the son of Maacha the daughter of Tolmai king of
@c    Gessur, the fourth Adonias the son of Aggith,

@c    3:3. The fifth Saphatias of Abital, the sixth Jethrahem of Egla his
@c    wife.

@c    3:4. So six sons were born to him in Hebron, where he reigned seven
@c    years and six months.  And in Jerusalem he reigned three and thirty
@c    years.

@c    3:5. And these sons were born to him in Jerusalem:  Simmaa, and Sobab,
@c    and Nathan, and Solomon, four of Bethsabee the daughter of Ammiel.

@c    3:6. Jebaar also and Elisama,

@c    3:7. And Eliphaleth, and Noge, and Nepheg, and Japhia,

@c    3:8. And Elisama, and Eliada, and Elipheleth, nine:

@c    3:9. All these the sons of David, beside the sons of the concubines:
@c    and they had a sister Thamar.

@c    The concubines. . .The inferior wives.

@c    3:10. And Solomon's son was Roboam:  whose son Abia begot Asa.  And his
@c    son was Josaphat,

@c    3:11. The father of Joram:  and Joram begot Ochozias, of whom was born
@c    Joas:

@c    3:12. And his son Amasias begot Azarias.  And Joathan the son of Azarias

@c    3:13. Begot Achaz, the father of Ezechias, of whom was born Manasses.

@c    3:14. And Manasses begot Amon the father of Josias.

@c    3:15. And the sons of Josias were, the firstborn Johanan, the second
@c    Joakim, the third Sedecias, the fourth Sellum.

@c    3:16. Of Joakim was born Jechonias, and Sedecias.

@c    3:17. The sons of Jechonias were Asir, Salathiel,

@c    3:18. Melchiram, Phadaia, Senneser and Jecemia, Sama, and Nadabia.

@c    3:19. Of Phadaia were born Zorobabel and Semei.  Zorobabel begot
@c    Mosollam, Hananias, and Salomith their sister:

@c    3:20. Hasaba also, and Ohol, and Barachias, and Hasadias, Josabhesed,
@c    five.

@c    3:21. And the son of Hananias was Phaltias the father of Jeseias, whose
@c    son was Raphaia.  And his son was Arnan, of whom was born Obdia, whose
@c    son was Sechenias.

@c    3:22. The son of Sechenias was Semeia, whose sons were Hattus, and
@c    Jegaal, and Baria, and Naaria, and Saphat, six in number.

@c    Six. . .Counting the father in the number.

@c    3:23. The sons of Naaria, Elioenai, and Ezechias, and Ezricam, three.

@c    3:24. The sons of Elioenai, Oduia, and Eliasub, and Pheleia, and Accub,
@c    and Johanan, and Dalaia, and Anani, seven.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 4


@c    Other genealogies of Juda and Simeon, and their victories.

@c    4:1. The sons of Juda:  Phares, Hesron, and Charmi and Hur, and Sobal.

@c    4:2. And Raia the son of Sobal begot Jahath, of whom were born Ahumai,
@c    and Laad.  These are the families of Sarathi.

@c    4:3. And this is the posterity of Etam:  Jezrahel, and Jesema, And
@c    Jedebos:  and the name of their sister was Asalelphuni.

@c    4:4. And Phanuel the father of Gedor, and Ezar the father of Hosa,
@c    these are the sons of Hur the firstborn of Ephratha the father of
@c    Bethlehem.

@c    4:5. And Assur the father of Thecua had two wives, Halaa and Naara:

@c    4:6. And Naara bore him Ozam, and Hepher, and Themani, and Ahasthari:
@c    these are the sons of Naara.

@c    4:7. And the sons of Halaa, Sereth, Isaar, and Ethnan.

@c    4:8. And Cos begot Anob, and Soboba, and the kindred of Aharehel the
@c    son of Arum.

@c    4:9. And Jabes was more honourable than any of his brethren, and his
@c    mother called his name Jabes, saying:  Because I bore him with sorrow.

@c    Jabes. . .That is, sorrowful.

@c    4:10. And Jabes called upon the God of Israel, saying:  If blessing thou
@c    wilt bless me, and wilt enlarge my borders, and thy hand be with me,
@c    and thou save me from being oppressed by evil.  And God granted him the
@c    things he prayed for.

@c    4:11. And Caleb the brother of Sua begot Mahir, who was the father of
@c    Esthon.

@c    4:12. And Esthon begot Bethrapha, and Phesse, and Tehinna father of the
@c    city of Naas:  these are the men of Recha.

@c    4:13. And the sons of Cenez were Othoniel, and Saraia.  And the sons of
@c    Othoniel, Hathath, and Maonathi.

@c    4:14. Maonathi begot Ophra, and Saraia begot Joab the father of the
@c    Valley of artificers:  for artificers were there.

@c    4:15. And the sons of Caleb the son of Jephone, were Hir, and Ela, and
@c    Naham.  And the sons of Ela:  Cenez.

@c    4:16. The sons also of Jaleleel:  Ziph, and Zipha, Thiria and Asrael.

@c    4:17. And the sons of Esra, Jether, and Mered, and Epher, and Jalon,
@c    and he begot Mariam, and Sammai, and Jesba the father of Esthamo.

@c    4:18. And his wife Judaia, bore Jared the father of Gedor, and Heber
@c    the father of Socho, and Icuthiel the father of Zanoe.  And these are
@c    the sons of Bethia the daughter of Pharao, whom Mered took to wife.

@c    4:19. And the sons of his wife Odaia the sister of Naham the father of
@c    Celia, Garmi, and Esthamo, who was of Machathi.

@c    4:20. The sons also of Simon, Amnon, and Rinna the son of Hanan, and
@c    Thilon.  And the sons of Jesi Zoheth, and Benzoheth.

@c    4:21. The sons of Sela the son of Juda:  Her the father of Lecha, and
@c    Laada the father of Maresa, and the families of the house of them that
@c    wrought fine linen in the House of oath.

@c    4:22. And he that made the sun to stand, and the men of Lying, and
@c    Secure, and Burning, who were princes in Moab, and who returned into
@c    Lahem.  Now these are things of old.

