@c    5:24. And these were the heads of the house of their kindred, Epher,
@c    and Jesi, and Eliel, and Esriel, and Jeremia, and Odoia, and Jediel,
@c    most valiant and powerful men, and famous chiefs in their families.

@c    5:25. But they forsook the God of their fathers, and went astray after
@c    the gods of the people of the land, whom God destroyed before them.

@c    5:26. And the God of Israel stirred up the spirit of Phul king of the
@c    Assyrians.  and the spirit of Thelgathphalnasar king of Assur:  and he
@c    carried away Ruben, and Gad, and the half tribe of Manasses, and
@c    brought them to Lahela, and to Habor, and to Ara, and to the river of
@c    Gozan, unto this day.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 6


@c    The genealogies of Levi, and of Aaron:  the cities of the Levites.

@c    6:1. The sons of Levi were Gerson, Caath, and Merari.

@c    6:2. The Sons of Caath:  Amram, Isaar, Hebron, and Oziel.

@c    6:3. The children of Amram:  Aaron, Moses, and Mary.  The Sons of Aaron:
@c    Nadab and Abiu, Eleazar and Ithamar.

@c    6:4. Eleazar begot Phinees, and Phinees begot Abisue,

@c    6:5. And Abisue begot Bocci, and Bocci begot Ozi.

@c    6:6. Ozi begot Zaraias, and Zaraias begot Maraioth.

@c    6:7. And Maraioth begot Amarias, and Amarias begot Achitob.

@c    6:8. Achitob begot Sadoc, and Sadoc begot Achimaas.

@c    6:9. Achimaas begot Azarias, Azarias begot Johanan,

@c    6:10. Johanan begot Azarias.  This is he that executed the priestly
@c    office in the house which Solomon built in Jerusalem.

@c    6:11. And Azarias begot Amarias, and Amarias begot Achitob.

@c    6:12. And Achitob begot Sadoc, and Sadoc begot Sellum,

@c    6:13. Sellum begot Helcias, and Helcias begot Azarias,

@c    6:14. Azarias begot Saraias, and Saraias begot Josedec.

@c    6:15. Now Josedec went out, when the Lord carried away Juda, and
@c    Jerusalem, by the hands of Nabuchodonosor.

@c    6:16. So the sons of Levi were Gerson, Caath, and Merari.

@c    6:17. And these are the names of the sons of Gerson:  Lobni and Semei.

@c    6:18. The sons of Caath:  Amram, and Isaar, and Hebron, and Oziel.

@c    6:19. The sons of Merari:  Moholi and Musi.  And these are the kindreds
@c    of Levi according to their families.

@c    6:20. Of Gerson:  Lobni his son, Jahath his son, Zamma his son,

@c    6:21. Joah his son, Addo his son, Zara his son, Jethrai his son.

@c    6:22. The sons of Caath, Aminadab his son, Core his son, Asir his son,

@c    6:23. Elcana his son, Abiasaph his son, Asir his son,

@c    6:24. Thahath his son, Uriel his son, Ozias his son, Saul his son.

@c    6:25. The sons of Elcana:  Amasai, and Achimoth.

@c    6:26. And Elcana.  The sons of Elcana:  Sophai his son, Nahath his son,

@c    6:27. Eliab his son, Jeroham his son, Elcana his son.

@c    6:28. The sons of Samuel:  the firstborn Vasseni, and Abia.

@c    6:29. And the sons of Merari, Moholi:  Lobni his son, Semei his son, Oza
@c    his son,

@c    6:30. Sammaa his son, Haggia his son, Asaia his son.

@c    6:31. These are they, whom David set over the singing men of the house
@c    of the Lord, after that the ark was placed.

@c    6:32. And they ministered before the tabernacle of the testimony, with
@c    singing, until Solomon built the house of the Lord in Jerusalem, and
@c    they stood according to their order in the ministry.

@c    6:33. And these are they that stood with their sons, of the sons of
@c    Caath, Hemam a singer, the son of Joel, the son of Sammuel,

@c    6:34. The son of Elcana, the son of Jeroham, the son of Eliel, the son
@c    of Thohu,

@c    6:35. The son of Suph, the son of Elcana, the son of Mahath, the son of
@c    Amasai,

@c    6:36. The son of Elcana, the son of Johel, the son of Azarias, the son
@c    of Sophonias,

@c    6:37. The son of Thahath, the son of Asir, the son of Abiasaph, the son
@c    of Core,

@c    6:38. The son of Isaar, the son of Caath, the son of Levi, the son of
@c    Israel.

@c    6:39. And his brother Asaph, who stood on his right hand, Asaph the son
@c    of Barachias, the son of Samaa.

@c    6:40. The son of Michael, the son of Basaia, the, son of Melchia.

@c    6:41. The son of Athanai, the son of Zara, the son of Adaia.

@c    6:42. The son of Ethan, the son of Zamma, the son of Semei.

@c    6:43. The son of Jeth, the son of Gerson, the son of Levi.

@c    6:44. And the sons of Merari their brethren, on the left hand, Ethan
@c    the son of Cusi, the son of Abdi, the son of Meloch,

@c    6:45. The son of Hasabia, the son of Amasai, the son of Helcias,

@c    6:46. The son of Amasai, the son of Boni, the son of Somer,

@c    6:47. The son of Moholi, the son of Musi, the son of Merari, the son of
@c    Levi.

@c    6:48. Their brethren also the Levites, who were appointed for all the
@c    ministry of the tabernacle of the house of the Lord.

@c    6:49. But Aaron and his sons offered burnt offerings upon the altar of
@c    holocausts, and upon the altar of incense, for every work of the holy
@c    of holies:  and to pray for Israel according to all that Moses the
@c    servant of God had commanded.

@c    6:50. And these are the sons of Aaron:  Eleazar his son, Phinees his
@c    son, Abisue his son,

@c    6:51. Bocci his son, Ozi his son, Zarahia his son,

@c    6:52. Meraioth his son, Amarias his son, Achitob his son,

@c    6:53. Sadoc his son, Achimaas his son.

@c    6:54. And these are their dwelling places by the towns and confines, to
@c    wit, of the sons of Aaron, of the families of the Caathites:  for they
@c    fell to them by lot.

@c    6:55. And they gave them Hebron in the land of Juda, and the suburbs
@c    thereof round about:

@c    6:56. But the fields of the city, and the villages to Caleb son of
@c    Jephone.

@c    6:57. And to the sons of Aaron they gave the cities for refuge Hebron,
@c    and Lobna, and the suburbs thereof,

@c    6:58. And Jether and Esthemo, with their suburbs, and Helon, and Dabir
@c    with their suburbs:

@c    6:59. Asan also, and Bethsames, with their suburbs.

@c    6:60. And out of the tribe of Benjamin:  Gabee and its suburbs, Almath
@c    with its suburbs, Anathoth also with its suburbs:  all their cities
@c    throughout their families were thirteen.

@c    6:61. And to the sons of Caath that remained of their kindred they gave
@c    out of the half tribe of Manasses ten cities in possession.

@c    6:62. And to the sons of Gerson by their families out of the tribe of
@c    Issachar, and out of the tribe of Aser, and out of the tribe of
