@c    6:68. Jecmaan also with its suburbs, and Beth-horon in like manner,

@c    6:69. Helon also with its suburbs, and Gethremmon in like manner,

@c    6:70. And out of the half tribe of Manasses, Aner and its suburbs,
@c    Baalam and its suburbs, to wit, to them that were left of the family of
@c    the sons of Caath.

@c    6:71. And to the sons of Gersom, out the kindred of the half tribe of
@c    Manasses, Gaulon, in Basan, and its suburbs, and Astharoth with its
@c    suburbs.

@c    6:72. Out of the tribe of Issachar, Cedes and its suburbs, and Dabereth
@c    with its suburbs;

@c    6:73. Ramoth also and its suburbs, and Anem with its suburbs.

@c    6:74. And out of the tribe of Aser:  Masal with its suburbs, and Abdon
@c    in like manner;

@c    6:75. Hucac also and its suburbs, and Rohol with its suburbs.

@c    6:76. And out of the tribe of Nephtali, Cedes in Galilee and its
@c    suburbs, Hamon with its suburbs, and Cariathaim, and its suburbs.

@c    6:77. And to the sons of Merari that remained:  out of the tribe of
@c    Zabulon, Remmono and its suburbs, and Thabor with its suburbs.

@c    6:78. Beyond the Jordan also over against Jericho, on the east side of
@c    the Jordan and out of the tribe of Ruben, Bosor in the wilderness with
@c    its suburbs, and Jassa with its suburbs;

@c    6:79. Cademoth also and its suburbs, and Mephaath with its suburbs;

@c    6:80. Moreover also out of the tribe of Gad, Ramoth in Galaad and its
@c    suburbs, and Manaim with its suburbs;

@c    6:81. Hesebon also with its suburbs, and Jazer with its suburbs.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 7


@c    Genealogies of Issachar, Benjamin, Nephtali, Manasses, Ephraim, and
@c    Aser.

@c    7:1. Now the sons of Issachar were Thola, and Phua, Jasub and Simeron,
@c    four.

@c    7:2. The sons of Thola:  Ozi and Raphaia, and Jeriel, and Jemai, and
@c    Jebsem, and Samuel, chiefs of the houses of their kindreds.  Of the
@c    posterity of Thola were numbered in the days of David, two and twenty
@c    thousand six hundred most valiant men.

@c    7:3. The sons of Ozi:  Izrahia, of whom were born Michael, and Obadia,
@c    and Joel, and Jesia, five all great men.

@c    7:4. And there were with them by their families and peoples, six and
@c    thirty thousand most valiant men ready for war:  for they had many wives
@c    and children.

@c    7:5. Their brethren also throughout all the house of Issachar, were
@c    numbered fourscore and seven thousand most valiant men for war.

@c    7:6. The sons of Benjamin were Bela, and Bechor, and Jadihel, three.

@c    7:7. The sons of Bela:  Esbon, and Ozi, and Ozial, and Jerimoth and
@c    Urai, five chiefs of their families, and most valiant warriors, and
@c    their number was twenty-two thousand and thirty-four.

@c    7:8. And the sons of Bechor were Zamira, and Joas, and Eliezer, and
@c    Elioenai, and Amai, and Jerimoth, and Abia, and Anathoth, and Almath:
@c    all these were the sons of Bechor.

@c    7:9. And they were numbered by the families, heads of their kindreds,
@c    most valiant men for war, twenty thousand and two hundred.

@c    7:10. And the son of Jadihel:  Balan.  And the sons of Balan:  Jehus and
@c    Benjamin, and Aod, and Chanana, and Zethan and Tharsis, and Ahisahar.

@c    7:11. All these were sons of Jadihel, heads of their kindreds, most
@c    valiant men, seventeen thousand and two hundred fifty to go out to war.

@c    7:12. Sepham also and Hapham the sons of Hir:  and Hasim the sons of
@c    Aher.

@c    7:13. And the sons of Nephtali were Jasiel, and Guni, and Jezer, and
@c    Sellum, sons of Bala.

@c    7:14. And the son of Manasses, Ezriel:  and his concubine the Syrian
@c    bore Machir the father of Galaad.

@c    7:15. And Machir took wives for his sons Happhim, and Saphan:  and he
@c    had a sister named Maacha:  the name of the second was Salphaad, and
@c    Salphaad had daughters.

@c    7:16. And Maacha the wife of Machir bore a son, and she called his name
@c    Phares:  and the name of his brother was Sares:  and his sons were Ulam
@c    and Recen.

@c    7:17. And the son of Ulam, Baden.  These are the sons of Galaad, the son
@c    of Machir, the son of Manasses.

@c    7:18. And his sister named Queen bore Goodlyman, and Abiezer, and
@c    Mohola.

@c    7:19. And the sons of Semida were Ahiu, and Sechem, and Leci and Aniam.

@c    7:20. And the sons of Ephraim were Suthala, Bared his son, Thahath his
@c    son, Elada his son, Thahath his son, and his son Zabad,

@c    7:21. And his son Suthala, and his son Ezer, and Elad:  and the men of
@c    Geth born in the land slew them, because they came down to invade their
@c    possessions.

@c    7:22. And Ephraim their father mourned many days, and his brethren came
@c    to comfort him.

@c    7:23. And he went in to his wife:  and she conceived and bore a son, and
@c    he called his name Beria, because he was born when it went evil with
@c    his house:

@c    Beria. . .This name signifies in evil, or in affliction.

@c    7:24. And his daughter was Sara, who built Bethoron, the nether and the
@c    upper, and Ozensara.

@c    7:25. And Rapha was his son, and Reseph, and Thale, of whom was born
@c    Thaan,

@c    7:26. Who begot Laadan:  and his son was Ammiud, who begot Elisama,

@c    7:27. Of whom was born Nun, who had Josue for his son.

@c    7:28. And their possessions and habitations were Bethel with her
@c    daughters, and eastward Noran, and westward Gazer and her daughters,
@c    Sichem also with her daughters, as far as Asa with her daughters.

@c    7:29. And by the borders of the sons of Manasses Bethsan and her
@c    daughters, Thanach and her daughters, Mageddo and her daughters:  Dor
@c    and her daughters:  in these dwelt the children of Joseph, the son of
@c    Israel.

@c    7:30. The children of Aser were Jemna, and Jesua, and Jessui, and
@c    Baria, and Sara their sister.

@c    7:31. And the sons of Baria:  Haber, and Melchiel:  he is the father of
@c    Barsaith.

@c    7:32. And Heber begot Jephlat, and Somer, and Hotham, and Suaa their
@c    sister.

@c    7:33. The sons of Jephlat:  Phosech, and Chamaal, and Asoth:  these are
@c    the sons of Jephlat.

@c    7:34. And the sons of Somer:  Ahi, and Roaga and Haba, and Aram.

@c    7:35. And the sons of Helem his brother:  Supha, and Jemna, and Selles,
@c    and Amal.

@c    7:36. The sons of Supha:  Sue, Hernapher, and Sual, and Beri, and Jamra.

@c    7:37. Bosor and Hod, and Samma, and Salusa, and Jethran, and Bera.

@c    7:38. The sons of Jether:  Jephone, and Phaspha, and Ara.

@c    7:39. And the sons of Olla:  Aree, and Haniel, and Resia.

@c    7:40. All these were sons of Aser, heads of their families, choice and
@c    most valiant captains of captains:  and the number of them that were of
@c    the age that was fit for war, was six and twenty thousand.



