@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 12


@c    Who followed David when he fled from Saul.  And who came to Hebron to
@c    make him king.

@c    12:1. Now these are they that came to David to Siceleg, while he yet
@c    fled from Saul the son of Cis, and they were most valiant and excellent
@c    warriors,

@c    12:2. Bending the bow, and using either hand in hurling stones with
@c    slings, and shooting arrows:  of the brethren of Saul of Benjamin.

@c    12:3. The chief was Ahiezer, and Joas, the sons of Samoa of Gabaath,
@c    and Jaziel, and Phallet the sons of Azmoth, and Beracha, and Jehu an
@c    Anathothite.

@c    12:4. And Samaias of Gabaon, the stoutest amongst the thirty and over
@c    the thirty; Jeremias, and Jeheziel and Johanan, and Jozabad of
@c    Gaderoth;

@c    12:5. And Eluzai, and Jerimuth, and Baalia, and Samaria, and Saphatia
@c    the Haruphite;

@c    12:6. Elcana, and Jesia, and Azareel, and Joezer, and Jesbaam of
@c    Carehim:

@c    12:7. And Joela, and Zabadia the sons of Jeroham of Gedor.

@c    12:8. From Gaddi also there went over to David, when he lay hid in the
@c    wilderness most valiant men, and excellent warriors, holding shield and
@c    spear:  whose faces were like the faces of a lion, and they were swift
@c    like the roebucks on the mountains.

@c    12:9. Ezer the chief, Obdias the second, Eliab the third,

@c    12:10. Masmana the fourth, Jeremias the fifth,

@c    12:11. Ethi the sixth, Eliel the seventh,

@c    12:12. Johanan the eighth, Elzebad the ninth,

@c    12:13. Jerenias the tenth, Machbani the eleventh,

@c    12:14. These were of the sons of Gad, captains of the army:  the least
@c    of them was captain over a hundred soldiers, and the greatest over a
@c    thousand.

@c    12:15. These are they who passed over the Jordan in the first month,
@c    when it is used to flow over its banks:  and they put to flight all that
@c    dwelt in the valleys both toward the east and toward the west.

@c    12:16. And there came also of the men of Benjamin, and of Juda to the
@c    hold, in which David abode.

@c    12:17. And David went out to meet them, and said:  If you are come
@c    peaceably to me to help me, let my heart be joined to you:  but if you
@c    plot against me for my enemies whereas I have no iniquity in my hands,
@c    let the God of our fathers see, and judge.

@c    12:18. But the spirit came upon Amasai the chief among thirty, and he
@c    said:  We are thine, O David, and for thee, O son of Isai:  peace, peace
@c    be to thee, and peace to thy helpers.  For thy God helpeth thee.  So
@c    David received them, and made them captains of the band.

@c    12:19. And there were some of Manasses that went over to David, when he
@c    came with the Philistines against Saul to fight:  but he did not fight
@c    with them:  because the lords of the Philistines taking counsel sent him
@c    back, saying:  With the danger of our heads he will return to his master
@c    Saul.

@c    12:20. So when he went back to Siceleg, there fled to him of Manasses,
@c    Ednas and Jozabad, and Jedihel, and Michael, and Ednas, and Jozabad,
@c    and Eliu, and Salathi, captains of thousands in Manasses.

@c    12:21. These helped David against the rovers:  for they were all most
@c    valiant men, and were made commanders in the army.

@c    12:22. Moreover day by day there came some to David to help him till
@c    they became a great number, like the army of God.

@c    12:23. And this is the number of the chiefs of the army who came to
@c    David, when he was in Hebron, to transfer to him the kingdom of Saul,
@c    according to the word of the Lord.

@c    12:24. The sons of Juda bearing shield and spear, six thousand eight
@c    hundred well appointed to war.

@c    12:25. Of the sons of Simeon valiant men for war, seven thousand one
@c    hundred.

@c    12:26. Of the sons of Levi, four thousand six hundred.

@c    12:27. And Joiada prince of the race of Aaron, and with him three
@c    thousand seven hundred.

@c    12:28. Sadoc also a young man of excellent disposition, and the house
@c    of his father, twenty-two principal men.

@c    12:29. And of the sons of Benjamin the brethren of Saul, three
@c    thousand:  for hitherto a great part of them followed the house of Saul.

@c    12:30. And of the sons of Ephraim twenty thousand eight hundred, men of
@c    great valour renowned in their kindreds.

@c    12:31. And of the half tribe of Manasses, eighteen thousand, every one
@c    by their names, came to make David king.

@c    12:32. Also of the sons of Issachar men of understanding, that knew all
@c    times to order what Israel should do, two hundred principal men:  and
@c    all the rest of the tribe followed their counsel.

@c    12:33. And of Zabulon such as went forth to battle, and stood in array
@c    well appointed with armour for war, there came fifty thousand to his
@c    aid, with no double heart.

@c    12:34. And of Nephtali, a thousand leaders:  and with them seven and
@c    thirty thousand, furnished with shield and spear.

@c    12:35. Of Dan also twenty-eight thousand six hundred prepared for
@c    battle.

@c    12:36. And of Aser forty thousand going forth to fight, and challenging
@c    in battle.

@c    12:37. And on the other side of the Jordan of the sons of Ruben, and of
@c    Gad, and of the half of the tribe of Manasses a hundred and twenty
@c    thousand, furnished with arms for war.

@c    12:38. All these men of war well appointed to fight, came with a
@c    perfect heart to Hebron, to make David king over all Israel:  and all
@c    the rest also of Israel, were of one heart to make David king.

@c    12:39. And they were there with David three days eating and drinking:
@c    for their brethren had prepared for them.

@c    12:40. Moreover they that were near them even as far as Issachar, and
@c    Zabulon, and Nephtali, brought loaves on asses, and on camels, and on
@c    mules, and on oxen, to eat:  meal, figs, raisins, wine, oil, and oxen,
@c    and sheep in abundance, for there was joy in Israel.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 13


@c    The ark is brought from Cariathiarim.  Oza for touching it is struck
@c    dead.

@c    13:1. David consulted with the captains of thousands, and of hundreds,
@c    and with all the commanders.

@c    13:2. And he said to all the assembly of Israel:  If it please you; and
@c    if the words which I speak come from the Lord our God, let us send to
@c    the rest of our brethren into all the countries of Israel, and to the
@c    priests, and the Levites, that dwell in the suburbs of the cities, to
@c    gather themselves to us,

@c    13:3. And let us bring again the ark of our God to us:  for we sought it
@c    not in the days of Saul.

@c    13:4. And all the multitude answered that it should be so:  for the word
@c    pleased all the people.

@c    13:5. So David assembled all Israel from Sihor of Egypt, even to the
@c    entering into Emath, to bring the ark of God from Cariathiarim.

@c    13:6. And David went up with all the men of Israel to the hill of
@c    Cariathiarim which is in Juda, to bring thence the ark of the Lord God
@c    sitting upon the cherubims, where his name is called upon.

@c    13:7. And they carried the ark of God upon a new cart out of the house
@c    of Abinadab.  And Oza and his brother drove the cart.

@c    13:8. And David and all Israel played before God with all their might
@c    with hymns, and with harps, and with psalteries, and timbrels, and
@c    cymbals, and trumpets,

@c    13:9. And when they came to the floor of Chidon, Oza put forth his
@c    hand, to hold up the ark:  for the ox being wanton had made it lean a
@c    little on one side.

@c    13:10. And the Lord was angry with Oza, and struck him, because he had
@c    touched the ark; and he died there before the Lord.

@c    13:11. And David was troubled because the Lord had divided Oza:  and he
@c    called that place the Breach of Oza to this day.

@c    13:12. And he feared God at that time, saying:  How can I bring in the
@c    ark of God to me?

@c    13:13. And therefore he brought it not home to himself, that is, into
@c    the city of David, but carried it aside into the house of Obededom the
@c    Gethite.

@c    13:14. And the ark of God remained in the house of Obededom three
@c    months:  and the Lord blessed his house, and all that he had.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 14


@c    David's house, and children:  his victories over the Philistines.

@c    14:1. And Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David, and cedar trees,
@c    and masons, and carpenters, to build him a house.

@c    14:2. And David perceived that the Lord had confirmed him king over
@c    Israel, and that his kingdom was exalted over his people Israel.

@c    14:3. And David took other wives in Jerusalem:  and he begot sons, and
@c    daughters.

@c    14:4. Now these are the names of them that were born to him in
@c    Jerusalem:  Samua, and Sobad, Nathan, and Solomon,

@c    14:5. Jebahar, and Elisua, and Eliphalet,

@c    14:6. And Noga, and Napheg, and Japhia,

@c    14:7. Elisama, and Baaliada, and Eliphalet.

@c    14:8. And the Philistines hearing that David was anointed king over all
@c    Israel, went all up to seek him:  and David heard of it, and went out
@c    against them.

@c    14:9. And the Philistines came and spread themselves in the vale of
@c    Raphaim.

@c    14:10. And David consulted the Lord, saying:  Shall I go up against the
@c    Philistines, and wilt thou deliver them into my hand?  And the Lord said
@c    to him:  Go up, and I will deliver them into thy hand.

@c    14:11. And when they were come to Baalpharasim, David defeated them
@c    there, and he said:  God hath divided my enemies by my hand, as waters
@c    are divided:  and therefore the name of that place was called
@c    Baalpharasim.

@c    14:12. And they left there their gods, and David commanded that they
@c    should be burnt.

@c    14:13. Another time also the Philistines made an irruption, and spread
@c    themselves abroad in the valley.

@c    14:14. And David consulted God again, and God said to him:  Go not up
@c    after them, turn away from them, and come upon them over against the
@c    pear trees.

@c    14:15. And when thou shalt hear the sound of one going in the tops of
@c    the pear trees, then shalt thou go out to battle.  For God is gone out
@c    before thee to strike the army of the Philistines.

@c    14:16. And David did as God had commanded him, and defeated the army of
@c    the Philistines, slaying them from Gabaon to Gazera.

@c    14:17. And the name of David became famous in all countries, and the
@c    Lord made all nations fear aim.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 15


@c    The ark is brought into the city of David, with great solemnity.  Michol
@c    derideth David's devotion.

@c    15:1. He made also houses for himself in the city of David:  and built a
@c    place for the ark of God, and pitched a tabernacle for it.

@c    15:2. Then David said:  No one ought to carry the ark of God, but the
@c    Levites, whom the Lord hath chosen to carry it, and to minister unto
@c    himself for ever.

@c    15:3. And he gathered all Israel together into Jerusalem, that the ark
@c    of God might be brought into its place, which he had prepared for it.

@c    15:4. And the sons of Aaron also, and the Levites.

@c    15:5. Of the children of Caath, Uriel was the chief, and his brethren a
@c    hundred and twenty.

@c    15:6. Of the sons of Merari, Asaia the chief, and his brethren two
@c    hundred and twenty.

@c    15:7. Of the sons of Gersom, Joel the chief, and his brethren a hundred
@c    and thirty.

@c    15:8. Of the sons of Elisaphan, Semeias the chief:  and his brethren two
@c    hundred.

@c    15:9. Of the sons of Hebron, Eliel the chief:  and his brethren eighty.

@c    15:10. Of the sons of Oziel, Aminadab the chief:  and his brethren a
@c    hundred and twelve.

@c    15:11. And David called Sadoc, and Abiathar the priests, and the
@c    Levites, Uriel, Asaia, Joel, Semeia, Eliel, and Aminadab:

@c    15:12. And he said to them:  You that are the heads of the Levitical
@c    families, be sanctified with your brethren, and bring the ark of the
@c    Lord the God of Israel to the place, which is prepared for it:

@c    15:13. Lest as the Lord at first struck us, because you were not
@c    present, the same should now also come to pass, by our doing some thing
@c    against the law.

@c    15:14. So the priests and the Levites were sanctified, to carry the ark
@c    of the Lord the God of Israel.

@c    15:15. And the sons of Levi took the ark of God as Moses had commanded,
@c    according to the word of the Lord, upon their shoulders, with the
