@c    blesseth the people, disposeth the offices of Levites, and maketh a
@c    psalm of praise to God.

@c    16:1. So they brought the ark of God, and set it in the midst of the
@c    tent, which David had pitched for it:  and they offered holocausts, and
@c    peace offerings before God.

@c    16:2. And when David had made an end of offering holocausts, and peace
@c    offerings, he blessed the people in the name of the Lord.

@c    16:3. And he divided to all and every one, both men and women, a loaf
@c    of bread, and a piece of roasted beef, and flour fried with oil.

@c    16:4. And he appointed Levites to minister before the ark of the Lord,
@c    and to remember his works, and to glorify, and praise the Lord God of
@c    Israel.

@c    16:5. Asaph the chief, and next after him Zacharias:  moreover Jahiel,
@c    and Semiramoth, and Jehiel, and Mathathias, and Eliab, and Banaias, and
@c    Obededom:  and Jehiel over the instruments of psaltery, and harps:  and
@c    Asaph sounded with cymbals:

@c    16:6. But Banaias, and Jaziel the priests, to sound the trumpet
@c    continually before the ark of the covenant of the Lord.

@c    16:7. In that day David made Asaph the chief to give praise to the Lord
@c    with his brethren.

@c    16:8. Praise ye the Lord, and call upon his name:  make known his doings
@c    among the nations.

@c    16:9. Sing to him, yea, sing praises to him:  and relate all his
@c    wondrous works.

@c    16:10. Praise ye his holy name:  let the heart of them rejoice, that
@c    seek the Lord.

@c    16:11. Seek ye the Lord, and his power:  seek ye his face evermore.

@c    16:12. Remember his wonderful works, which he hath done:  his signs, and
@c    the judgments of his mouth.

@c    16:13. O ye seed of Israel his servants, ye children of Jacob his
@c    chosen.

@c    16:14. He is the Lord our God:  his judgments are in all the earth.

@c    16:15. Remember for ever his covenant:  the word, which he commanded to
@c    a thousand generations.

@c    16:16. The covenant which he made with Abraham:  and his oath to Isaac.

@c    16:17. And he appointed the same to Jacob for a precept:  and to Israel
@c    for an everlasting covenant:

@c    16:18. Saying:  To thee will I give the land of Chanaan:  the lot of your
@c    inheritance.

@c    16:19. When they were but a small number:  very few and sojourners in
@c    it.

@c    16:20. And they passed from nation to nation:  and from a kingdom to
@c    another people.

@c    16:21. He suffered no man to do them wrong:  and reproved kings for
@c    their sake.

@c    16:22. Touch not my anointed:  and do no evil to my prophets.

@c    16:23. Sing ye to the Lord, all the earth:  shew forth from day to day
@c    his salvation.

@c    16:24. Declare his glory among the Gentiles:  his wonders among all
@c    people.

@c    16:25. For the Lord is great and exceedingly to be praised:  and he is
@c    to be feared above all gods.

@c    16:26. For all the gods of the nations are idols:  but the Lord made the
@c    heavens.

@c    16:27. Praise and magnificence are before him:  strength and joy in his
@c    place.

@c    16:28. Bring ye to the Lord, O ye families of the nations:  bring ye to
@c    the Lord glory and empire.

@c    16:29. Give to the Lord glory to his name, bring up sacrifice, and come
@c    ye in his sight:  and adore the Lord in holy becomingness.

@c    16:30. Let all the earth be moved at his presence:  for he hath founded
@c    the world immoveable.

@c    16:31. Let the heavens rejoice, and the earth be glad:  and let them say
@c    among the nations:  The Lord hath reigned.

@c    16:32. Let the sea roar, and the fulness thereof:  let the fields
@c    rejoice, and all things that are in them.

@c    16:33. Then shall the trees of the wood give praise before the Lord:
@c    because he is come to judge the earth.

@c    16:34. Give ye glory to the Lord, for he is good:  for his mercy
@c    endureth for ever.

@c    16:35. And say ye:  Save us, O God our savior:  and gather us together,
@c    and deliver us from the nations, that we may give glory to thy holy
@c    name, and may rejoice in singing thy praises.

@c    16:36. Blessed be the Lord the God of Israel from eternity to eternity:
@c    and let all the people say Amen, and a hymn to God.

@c    16:37. So he left there before the ark of the covenant of the Lord,
@c    Asaph and his brethren to minister in the presence of the ark
@c    continually day by day, and in their courses.

@c    16:38. And Obededom, with his brethren sixty-eight:  and Obededom the
@c    son of Idithun, and Hosa he appointed to be porters.

@c    16:39. And Sadoc the priest, and his brethren priests, before the
@c    tabernacle of the Lord in the high place, which was in Gabaon.

@c    16:40. That they should offer holocausts to the Lord upon the altar of
@c    holocausts continually, morning and evening, according to all that is
@c    written in the law of the Lord, which he commanded Israel.

@c    16:41. And after him Heman, and Idithun, and the rest that were chosen,
@c    every one by his name to give praise to the Lord:  because his mercy
@c    endureth for ever.

@c    16:42. And Heman and Idithun sounded the trumpet, and played on the
@c    cymbals, and all kinds of musical instruments to sing praises to God:
@c    and the sons of Idithun he made porters.

@c    16:43. And all the people returned to their houses:  and David to bless
@c    also his own house.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 17


@c    David's purpose to build a temple, is rewarded by most ample promises:
@c    David's thanksgiving.

@c    17:1. Now when David was dwelling in his house, he said to Nathan the
@c    prophet:  Behold I dwell in a house of cedar:  and the ark of the
@c    covenant of the Lord is under skins.

@c    17:2. And Nathan said to David:  Do all that is in thy heart:  for God is
@c    with thee.

@c    17:3. Now that night the word of God came to Nathan, saying:

@c    17:4. Go, and speak to David my servant:  Thus saith the Lord:  Thou
@c    shalt not build me a house to dwell in.

@c    17:5. For I have not remained in a house from the time that I brought
@c    up Israel, to this day:  but I have been always changing places in a
@c    tabernacle, and in a tent,

@c    17:6. Abiding with all Israel.  Did I ever speak to any one, of all the
@c    judges of Israel whom I charged to feed my people, saying:  Why have you
@c    not built me a house of cedar?

@c    17:7. Now therefore thus shalt thou say to my servant David:  Thus saith
@c    the Lord of hosts:  I took thee from the pastures, from following the
@c    flock, that thou shouldst be ruler of my people Israel.

@c    17:8. And I have been with thee whithersoever thou hast gone:  and have
@c    slain all thy enemies before thee, and have made thee a name like that
@c    of one of the great ones that are renowned in the earth.

@c    17:9. And I have given a place my people Israel:  they shall be planted,
@c    and shall dwell therein, and shall be moved no more, neither shall the
@c    children of iniquity waste them, as at the beginning,

@c    17:10. Since the days that I gave judges to my people Israel, and have
@c    humbled all thy enemies.  And I declare to thee, that the Lord will
@c    build thee a house.

@c    17:11. And when thou shalt have ended thy days to go to thy fathers, I
@c    will raise up thy seed after thee, which shall be of thy sons:  and I
@c    will establish his kingdom.

@c    17:12. He shall build me a house, and I will establish his throne for
@c    ever.

@c    17:13. I will be to him a father, and he shall be to me a son:  and I
@c    will not take my mercy away from him, as I took it from him that was
@c    before thee.

@c    17:14. But I will settle him in my house, and in my kingdom for ever:
@c    and his throne shall be most firm for ever.

@c    17:15. According to all these words, and according to all this vision,
@c    so did Nathan speak to David.

@c    17:16. And king David came and sat before the Lord, and said:  Who am I,
@c    O Lord God, and what is my house, that thou shouldst give such things
@c    to me?

@c    17:17. But even this hath seemed little in thy sight, and therefore
@c    thou hast also spoken concerning the house of thy servant for the time
@c    to come:  and hast made me remarkable above all men, O Lord God.

@c    17:18. What can David add more, seeing thou hast thus glorified thy
@c    servant, and known him?

@c    17:19. O Lord, for thy servant's sake, according to thy own heart, thou
@c    hast shewn all this magnificence, and wouldst have all the great things
@c    to be known.

@c    17:20. O Lord there is none like thee:  and here is no other God beside
@c    thee, of all whom we have heard of with our ears.

@c    17:21. For what other nation is there upon earth like thy people
@c    Israel, whom God went to deliver, and make a people for himself, and by
@c    his greatness and terrors cast out nations before their face whom he
@c    had delivered out of Egypt?

@c    17:22. And thou hast made thy people Israel to be thy own people for
@c    ever, and thou, O Lord, art become their God.

@c    17:23. Now therefore, O Lord, let the word which thou hast spoken to
@c    thy servant, and concerning his house, be established for ever, and do
@c    as thou hast said.

@c    17:24. And let thy name remain and be magnified for ever:  and let it be
@c    said:  The Lord of hosts is God of Israel, and the house of David his
@c    servant remaineth before him.

@c    17:25. For thou, O Lord my God, hast revealed to the ear of thy
@c    servant, that thou wilt build him a house:  and therefore thy servant
@c    hath found confidence to pray before thee.

@c    17:26. And now O Lord, thou art God:  and thou hast promised to thy
@c    servant such great benefits.

@c    17:27. And thou hast begun to bless the house of thy servant, that it
@c    may be always before thee:  for seeing thou blessest it, O Lord, it
@c    shall be blessed for ever.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 18


@c    David's victories.  His chief officers.

@c    18:1. And it came to pass after this, that David defeated the
@c    Philistines, and humbled them, and took away Geth, and her daughters
@c    out of the hands of the Philistines,

@c    18:2. And he defeated Moab, and the Moabites were made David's
