@c    18:5. And the Syrians of Damascus came also to help Adarezer king of
@c    Soba:  and David slew of them likewise two and twenty thousand men.

@c    18:6. And he put a garrison in Damascus, that Syria also should serve
@c    him, and bring gifts.  And the Lord assisted him in all things to which
@c    he went.

@c    18:7. And David took the golden quivers which the servants of Adarezer
@c    had, and he brought them to Jerusalem.

@c    18:8. Likewise out of Thebath and Chun, cities of Adarezer, he brought
@c    very much brass, of which Solomon made the brazen sea, and the pillars,
@c    and the vessels of brass.

@c    18:9. Now when Thou king of Hemath heard that David had defeated all
@c    the army of Adarezer king of Soba,

@c    18:10. He sent Adoram his son to king David to desire peace of him, and
@c    to congratulate him that he had defeated and overthrown Adarezer:  for
@c    Thou was an enemy to Adarezer.

@c    18:11. And all the vessels of gold, and silver and brass king David
@c    consecrated to the Lord, with the silver and gold which he had taken
@c    from all the nations, as well from Edom, and from Moab, and from the
@c    sons of Ammon, as from the Philistines, and from Amalec.

