@c    and the Phelethi:  and the sons of David were chief about the king.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 19


@c    The Ammonites abuse David's ambassadors:  both they and their
@c    confederates are overthrown.

@c    19:1. Now it came to pass that Naas the king of the children of Ammon
@c    died, and his son reigned in his stead.

@c    19:2. And David said:  I will shew kindness to Hanon the son of Naas:
@c    for his father did a favour tome.  And David sent messengers to comfort
@c    him upon the death of his father.  But when they were come into the land
@c    of the children of Ammon, to comfort Hanon,

@c    19:3. The princes of the children of Ammon said to Hanon:  Thou thinkest
@c    perhaps that David to do honour to thy father hath sent comforters to
@c    thee:  and thou dost not take notice, that his servants are come to thee
@c    to consider, and search, and spy out thy land.

@c    19:4. Wherefore Hanon shaved the heads and beards of the servants of
@c    David, and cut away their garments from the buttocks to the feet, and
@c    sent them away.

@c    19:5. And when they were gone, they sent word to David, who sent to
@c    meet them (for they had suffered a great affront) and ordered them to
@c    stay at Jericho till their beards grew and then to return.

@c    19:6. And when the children of Ammon saw that they had done an injury
@c    to David, Hanon and the rest of the people sent a thousand talents of
@c    silver, to hire them chariots and horsemen out of Mesopotamia and out
@c    of Syria Maacha, and out of Soba.

@c    19:7. And they hired two and thirty thousand chariots, and the king of
@c    Maacha, with his people.  And they came and camped over against Medaba.
@c    And the children of Ammon gathered themselves together out of their
@c    cities, and came to battle.

@c    19:8. And when David heard of it, he sent Joab, and all the army of
@c    valiant men:

@c    19:9. And the children of Ammon came out and put their army in array
@c    before the gate of the city:  and the kings, that were come to their
@c    aid, stood apart in the field.

@c    19:10. Wherefore Joab understanding that the battle was set against him
@c    before and behind, chose out the bravest men of all Israel, and marched
@c    against the Syrians,

@c    19:11. And the rest of the people he delivered into the hand of Abisai
@c    his brother, and they went against the children of Ammon.

@c    19:12. And he said:  If the Syrians be too strong for me, then thou
@c    shalt help me:  but if the children of Ammon be too strong for thee, I
@c    will help thee.

@c    19:13. Be of good courage and let us behave ourselves manfully for our
@c    people, and for the cities of our God:  and the Lord will do that which
@c    is good in his sight.

@c    19:14. So Joab and the people that were with him, went against the
@c    Syrians to the battle:  and he put them to flight.

@c    19:15. And the children of Ammon seeing that the Syrians were fled,
@c    they likewise fled from Abisai his brother, and went into the city:  and
@c    Joab also returned to Jerusalem.

@c    19:16. But the Syrians seeing that they had fallen before Israel, sent
@c    messengers, and brought to them the Syrians that were beyond the river:
@c    and Sophach, general of the army of Adarezer, was their leader.

@c    19:17. And it was told David, and he gathered together all Israel, and
@c    passed the Jordan, and came upon them, and put his army in array
@c    against them, and they fought with him.

@c    19:18. But the Syrian fled before Israel:  and David slew of the Syrians
@c    seven thousand chariots, and forty thousand footmen, and Sophach the
@c    general of the army.

@c    Seven thousand chariots. . .That is, of men who fought in chariots.

@c    19:19. And when the servants of Adarezer saw themselves overcome by
@c    Israel, they went over to David, and served him:  and Syria would not
@c    help the children of Ammon any more.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 20


@c    Rabba is taken.  Other victories over the Philistines.

@c    20:1. And it came to pass after the course of a year, at the time that
@c    kings go out to battle, Joab gathered together an army and the strength
@c    of the troops, and wasted the land of the children of Ammon:  and went
@c    and besieged Rabba.  But David stayed at Jerusalem, when Joab smote
@c    Rabba, and destroyed it.

@c    20:2. And David took the crown of Melchom from his head, and found in
@c    it a talent weight of gold, and most precious stones, and he made
@c    himself a diadem of it:  he took also the spoils of the city which were
@c    very great.

@c    20:3. And the people that were therein he brought out:  and made
@c    harrows, and sleds, and chariots of iron to go over them, so that they
@c    were cut and bruised to pieces:  in this manner David dealt with all the
@c    cities of the children of Ammon:  and he returned with all his people to
@c    Jerusalem.

@c    20:4. After this there arose a war at Gazer against the Philistines:  in
@c    which Sabachai the Husathite slew Saphai of the race of Raphaim, and
@c    humbled them.

@c    20:5. Another battle also was fought against the Philistines, in which
@c    Adeodatus the son of Saltus a Bethlehemite slew the brother of Goliath
@c    the Gethite, the staff of whose spear was like a weaver's beam.

@c    20:6. There was another battle also in Geth, in which there was a man
@c    of great stature, whose fingers and toes were four and twenty, six on
@c    each hand and foot:  who also was born of the stock of Rapha.

@c    20:7. He reviled Israel:  but Jonathan the son of Samaa the brother of
@c    David slew him.  These were the sons of Rapha in Geth, who fell by the
@c    hand of David and his servants.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 21


@c    David's sin in numbering the people is punished by a pestilence:  which
@c    ceaseth upon his offering sacrifice in the thrashingfloor of Ornan.

@c    21:1. And Satan rose up against Israel:  and moved David to number
@c    Israel.

@c    21:2. And David said to Joab, and to the rulers of the people:  Go, and
@c    number Israel from Bersabee even to Dan, and bring me the number of
@c    them that I may know it.

@c    21:3. And Joab answered:  The Lord make his people a hundred times more
@c    than they are:  but, my lord the king, are they not all thy servants:
@c    why doth my lord seek this thing, which may be imputed as a sin to
@c    Israel?

@c    21:4. But the king's word rather prevailed:  and Joab departed, and went
@c    through all Israel:  and returned to Jerusalem.

@c    21:5. And he gave David the number of them, whom he had surveyed:  and
@c    all the number of Israel was found to be eleven hundred thousand men
@c    that drew the sword:  and of Juda four hundred and seventy thousand
@c    fighting men.

@c    The number, etc. . .The difference of the numbers here and 2 Kings 24.
@c    is to be accounted for, by supposing the greater number to be that
@c    which was really found, and the lesser to be that which Joab gave in.

@c    21:6. But Levi and Benjamin he did not number:  for Joab unwillingly
@c    executed the king's orders.

@c    21:7. And God was displeased with this thing that was commanded:  and he
@c    struck Israel.

@c    21:8. And David said to God:  I have sinned exceedingly in doing this:  I
@c    beseech thee take away the iniquity of thy servant, for I have done
@c    foolishly.

@c    21:9. And the Lord spoke to Gad the seer of David, saying:

@c    21:10. Go, and speak to David, and tell him:  Thus saith the Lord:  I
@c    give thee the choice of three things:  choose one which thou wilt, and I
@c    will do it to thee.

@c    21:11. And when Gad was come to David, he said to him:  Thus saith the
@c    Lord:  choose which thou wilt:

@c    21:12. Either three years famine:  or three months to flee from thy
@c    enemies, and not to be able to escape their sword:  or three days to
@c    have the sword of the Lord, and pestilence in the land, and the angel
@c    of the Lord destroying in all the coasts of Israel:  now therefore see
@c    what I shall answer him who sent me.

@c    Three years famine. . .Which joined with the three foregoing years of
@c    famine mentioned, 2 Kings 21. and the seventh year of the land's
@c    resting, would make up the seven years proposed by the prophet, 2 Kings
@c    24.13.

@c    21:13. And David said to Gad:  I am on every side in a great strait:  but
@c    it is better for me to fall into the hands of the Lord, for his mercies
@c    are many, than into the hands of men.

@c    21:14. So the Lord sent a pestilence upon Israel.  And there fell of
@c    Israel seventy thousand men.

@c    21:15. And he sent an angel to Jerusalem, to strike it:  and as he was
@c    striking it, the Lord beheld, and took pity for the greatness of the
@c    evil:  and said to the angel that destroyed:  It is enough, now stop thy
@c    hand.  And the angel of the Lord stood by the thrashingfloor of Ornan
@c    the Jebusite.

@c    Ornan. . .Otherwise Areuna.

@c    21:16. And David lifting up his eyes, saw the angel of the Lord
@c    standing between heaven and earth, with a drawn sword in his hand,
@c    turned against Jerusalem:  and both he and the ancients clothed in
@c    haircloth, fell down flat on the ground.

@c    21:17. And David said to God:  Am not I he that commanded the people to
@c    be numbered?  It is I that have sinned:  it is I that have done the evil:
@c    but as for this flock, what hath it deserved?  O Lord my God, let thy
@c    hand be turned, I beseech thee, upon me, and upon my father's house:
@c    and let not thy people be destroyed.

@c    21:18. And the angel of the Lord commanded Gad to tell David, to go up,
@c    and build an altar to the Lord God in the thrashingfloor of Ornan the
@c    Jebusite.

@c    21:19. And David went up, according to the word of Gad, which he spoke
@c    to him in the name of the Lord.

@c    21:20. Now when Ornan looked up, and saw the angel, he and his four
@c    sons hid themselves:  for at that time he was thrashing wheat in the
@c    floor.

@c    21:21. And as David was coming to Ornan, Ornan saw him, and went out of
@c    the thrashingfloor to meet him, and bowed down to him with his face to
@c    the ground.

@c    21:22. And David said to him:  Give me this place of thy thrashingfloor,
@c    that I may build therein an altar to the Lord:  but thou shalt take of
@c    me as much money as it is worth, that the plague may cease from the
@c    people.

@c    21:23. And Ornan said to David:  Take it, and let my lord the king do
@c    all that pleaseth him:  and moreover the oxen also I give for a
@c    holocaust, and the drays for wood, and the wheat for the sacrifice:  I
@c    will give it all willingly.

@c    21:24. And king David said to him:  It shall not be so, but I will give
@c    thee money as much as it is worth:  for I must not take it from thee,
@c    and so offer to the Lord holocausts free cost.

@c    21:25. So David gave to Ornan for the place, six hundred sicles of gold
@c    of just weight.

@c    Six hundred sicles, etc. . .This was the price of the whole place, on
@c    which the temple was afterwards built; but the price of the oxen was
@c    fifty sicles of silver.  2 Kings 24.24.

@c    21:26. And he built there an altar to the Lord:  and he offered
@c    holocausts, and peace offerings, and he called upon the Lord, and he
@c    heard him by sending fire from heaven upon the altar of the holocaust.

@c    21:27. And the Lord commanded the angel:  and he put up his sword again
@c    into the sheath.

@c    21:28. And David seeing that the Lord had heard him in the
@c    thrashingfloor of Ornan the Jebusite, forthwith offered victims there.

@c    21:29. But the tabernacle of the Lord, which Moses made in the desert,
@c    and the altar of holocausts, was at that time in the high place of
@c    Gabaon.

@c    21:30. And David could not go to the altar there to pray to God:  for he
@c    was seized with an exceeding great fear, seeing the sword of the angel
@c    of the Lord.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 22


@c    David having prepared all necessaries, chargeth Solomon to build the
@c    temple and the princes to assist him.

@c    22:1. Then David said:  This is the house of God, And this is the altar
@c    for the holocaust of Israel.

@c    22:2. And he commanded to gather together all the proselytes of the
@c    land of Israel, and out of them he appointed stonecutters to hew stones
@c    and polish them, to build the house of God.

@c    22:3. And David prepared in abundance iron for the nails of the gates,
@c    and for the closures and joinings:  and of brass an immense weight.

@c    22:4. And the cedar trees were without number, which the Sidonians, and
@c    Tyrians brought to David.

@c    22:5. And David said:  Solomon my son is very young and tender, and the
@c    house which I would have to be built to the Lord, must be such as to be
@c    renowned in all countries:  therefore I will prepare him necessaries.
@c    And therefore before his death he prepared all the charges.

@c    22:6. And he called for Solomon his son:  and commanded him to build a
@c    house to the Lord the God of Israel.

@c    22:7. And David said to Solomon:  My son, it was my desire to have built
@c    a house to the name of the Lord my God.

@c    22:8. But the word of the Lord came to me, saying:  Thou hast shed much
@c    blood, and fought many battles, so thou cannot not build house to my
@c    name, after shedding so much blood before me:

@c    22:9. The son, that shall be born to thee, shall be a most quiet man:
@c    for I will make him rest from all his enemies round about:  and
@c    therefore he shall be called Peaceable:  and I will give peace and
@c    quietness to Israel all his days.

@c    22:10. He shall build a house to my name, and he shall be a son to me,
@c    and I will be a father to him:  and I will establish the throne of his
@c    kingdom over Israel for ever.

@c    22:11. Now then, my son, the Lord be with thee, and do thou prosper,
@c    and build the house to the Lord thy God, as he hath spoken of thee.

@c    22:12. The Lord also give thee wisdom and understanding, that thou
@c    mayest be able to rule Israel, and to keep the law of the Lord thy God.

@c    22:13. For then thou shalt be able to prosper, if thou keep the
@c    commandments, and judgments, which the Lord commanded Moses to teach
@c    Israel:  take courage and act manfully, fear not, nor be dismayed.

@c    22:14. Behold I in my poverty have prepared the charges of the house of
@c    the Lord, of gold a hundred thousand talents, and of silver a million
@c    of talents:  but of brass, and of iron there is no weight, for the
@c    abundance surpasseth all account:  timber also and stones I have
@c    prepared for all the charges.

@c    22:15. Thou hast also workmen in abundance, hewers of stones, and
@c    masons, and carpenters, and of all trades the most skilful in their
@c    work,

@c    22:16. In gold, and in silver, and in brass, and in iron, whereof there
@c    is no number.  Arise then, and be doing, and the Lord will be with thee.

@c    22:17. David also charged all the princes of Israel, to help Solomon
@c    his son,

@c    22:18. Saying:  You see, that the Lord your God is with you, and hath
@c    given you rest round about, and hath delivered all your enemies into
@c    your hands, and the land is subdued before the Lord, and before his
@c    people.

@c    22:19. Give therefore your hearts and your souls, to seek the Lord your
@c    God and arise, and build a sanctuary to the Lord God, that the ark of
@c    the covenant of the Lord, and the vessels consecrated to the Lord, may
@c    be brought into the house, which is built to the name of the Lord.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 23


@c    David appointeth Solomon king.  The distribution of the Levites and
@c    their offices.

@c    23:1. David being old and full of days, made Solomon his son king over
@c    Israel.

@c    23:2. And he gathered together all the princes of Israel, and the
@c    priests and Levites.

@c    23:3. And the Levites were numbered from the age of thirty years, and
@c    upwards:  and there were found of them thirty-eight thousand men.

@c    23:4. Of these twenty-four thousand were chosen, and distributed unto
@c    the ministry of the house of the Lord:  and six thousand were the
@c    overseers and judges.

@c    23:5. Moreover four thousand were porters:  and as many singers singing
@c    to the Lord with the instruments, which he had made to sing with.

@c    23:6. And David distributed them into courses by the families of the
@c    sons of Levi, to wit, of Gerson, and of Caath, and of Merari.

@c    23:7. The sons of Gerson were Leedan and Semei.

@c    23:8. The sons of Leedan:  the chief Jahiel, and Zethan, and Joel,
@c    three.

@c    23:9. The sons of Semei:  Salomith, and Hosiel, and Aran, three:  these
@c    were the heads of the families of Leedan.

@c    23:10. And the sons of Semei were Leheth, and Ziza, and Jaus, and
@c    Baria:  these were the sons of Semei, four.

@c    23:11. And Leheth was the first, Ziza the second:  but Jaus and Baria
@c    had not many children, and therefore they were counted in one family,
@c    and in one house.

@c    23:12. The sons of Caath were Amram, and Isaar, Hebron, and Oziel,
@c    four.

@c    23:13. The sons of Amram, Aaron, and Moses.  And Aaron was separated to
@c    minister in the holy of holies, he and his sons for ever, and to burn
@c    incense before the Lord, according to his ceremonies, and to bless his
@c    name for ever.

@c    23:14. The sons also of Moses, the man of God, were numbered in the
@c    tribe of Levi.

@c    23:15. The sons of Moses were Gersom and Eliezer:

@c    23:16. The sons of Gersom:  Subuel the first.

@c    23:17. And the sons of Eliezer were:  Rohobia the first:  and Eliezer had
@c    no more sons.  But the sons of Rohobia were multiplied exceedingly.

@c    23:18. The sons of Isaar:  Salomith the first.

@c    23:19. The sons of Hebron:  Jeriau the first, Amarias the second,
@c    Jahaziel the third, Jecmaam the fourth.

@c    23:20. The sons of Oziel:  Micha the first, Jesia the second.

@c    23:21. The sons of Merari:  Moholi, and Musi.  The sons of Moholi:
@c    Eleazar and Cis.

@c    23:22. And Eleazar died, and had no sons but daughters:  and the sons of
@c    Cis their brethren took them.

@c    23:23. The sons of Musi:  Moholi, and Eder, and Jerimoth, three.

@c    23:24. These are the sons of Levi in their kindreds and families,
@c    princes by their courses, and the number of every head that did the
@c    works of the ministry of the house of the Lord from twenty years old
@c    and upward.

@c    23:25. For David said:  The Lord the God of Israel hath given rest to
@c    his people, and a habitation in Jerusalem for ever.

@c    23:26. And it shall not be the office of the Levites to carry any more
@c    the tabernacle, and all the vessels for the service thereof.

@c    23:27. So according to the last precepts of David, the sons of Levi are
@c    to be numbered from twenty years old and upward.

@c    23:28. And they are to be under the hand of the sons of Aaron for the
@c    service of the house of the Lord, in the porches, and in the chambers,
@c    and in the place of purification, and in the sanctuary, and in all the
@c    works of the ministry of the temple of the Lord.

@c    23:29. And the priests have the charge of the loaves of proposition,
@c    and of the sacrifice of fine flour, and of the unleavened cakes, and of
@c    the fryingpan, and of the roasting, and of every weight and measure.

@c    23:30. And the Levites are to stand in the morning to give thanks, and
@c    to sing praises to the Lord:  and in like manner in the evening,

@c    23:31. As well in the oblation of the holocausts of the Lord, as in the
@c    sabbaths and in the new moons, and the rest of the solemnities,
@c    according to the number and ceremonies prescribed for every thing,
@c    continually before the Lord.

@c    23:32. And let them keep the observances of the tabernacle of the
@c    covenant, and the ceremonies of the sanctuary, and the charge of the
@c    sons of Aaron their brethren, that they may minister in the house of
@c    the Lord.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 24


@c    The divisions of the priests into four and twenty courses, to serve in
@c    the temple:  the chiefs of the Levites.

@c    24:1. Now these were the divisions of the sons of Aaron:  The sons of
@c    Aaron:  Nadab, and Abiu, and Eleazar, and Ithamar.

@c    24:2. But Nadab and Abiu died before their father, and had no children:
@c    so Eleazar, and Ithamar did the office of the priesthood.

@c    24:3. And David distributed them, that is, Sadoc of the sons of
@c    Eleazar, and Ahimelech of the sons of Ithamar, according to their
@c    courses and ministry.

@c    24:4. And there were found many more of the sons of Eleazar among the
@c    principal men, than of the sons of Ithamar.  And he divided them so,
@c    that there were of the sons of Eleazar, sixteen chief men by their
@c    families:  and of the sons of Ithamar eight by their families and
@c    houses.

@c    24:5. And he divided both the families one with the other by lot:  for
@c    there were princes of the sanctuary, and princes of God, both of the
@c    sons of Eleazar, and of the sons of Ithamar.

@c    24:6. And Semeias the son of Nathanael the scribe a Levite, wrote them
@c    down before the king and the princes, and Sadoc the priest, and
@c    Ahimelech the son of Abiathar, and the princes also of the priestly and
@c    Levitical families:  one house, which was over the rest, of Eleazar:  and
@c    another house, which had the rest under it, of Ithamar.

@c    24:7. Now the first lot came forth to Joiarib, the second to Jedei,

@c    24:8. The third to Harim, the fourth to Seorim,

@c    24:9. The fifth to Melchia, the sixth to Maiman,

@c    24:10. The seventh to Accos, the eighth to Abia,

@c    24:11. The ninth to Jesua, the tenth to Sechenia,

@c    24:12. The eleventh to Eliasib, the twelfth to Jacim,

@c    24:13. The thirteenth to Hoppha, the fourteenth to Isbaab,

@c    24:14. The fifteenth to Belga, the sixteenth to Emmer,

@c    24:15. The seventeenth to Hezir, the eighteenth to Aphses,

@c    24:16. The nineteenth to Pheteia, the twentieth to Hezechiel,

@c    24:17. The one and twentieth to Jachin, the two and twentieth to Gamul,

@c    24:18. The three and twentieth to Dalaiau, the four and twentieth to
@c    Maaziau.

@c    24:19. These are their courses according to their ministries, to come
@c    into the house of the Lord, and according to their manner under the
@c    hand of Aaron their father:  as the Lord the God of Israel had
@c    commanded.

@c    24:20. Now of the rest of the sons of Levi, there was of the sons of
@c    Amram, Subael:  and of the sons of Subael, Jehedeia.

@c    24:21. Also of the sons of Rohobia the chief Jesias.

@c    24:22. And the son of Isaar Salemoth, and the son of Salemoth Jahath:

@c    24:23. And his son Jeriau the first, Amarias the second, Jahaziel the
