@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 26


@c    The divisions of the porters.  Offices of other Levites.

@c    26:1. And the divisions of the porters:  of the Corites Meselemia, the
@c    son of Core, of the sons of Asaph.

@c    26:2. The sons of Meselemia:  Zacharias the firstborn, Jadihel the
@c    second, Zabadias the third, Jathanael the fourth,

@c    26:3. Elam the fifth, Johanan the sixth, Elioenai the seventh.

@c    26:4. And the sons of Obededom, Semeias the firstborn, Jozabad the
@c    second, Joaha the third, Sachar the fourth, Nathanael the fifth,

@c    26:5. Ammiel the sixth, Issachar the seventh, Phollathi the eighth:  for
@c    the Lord had blessed him.

@c    26:6. And to Semei his son were born sons, heads of their families:  for
@c    they were men of great valour.

@c    26:7. The sons then of Semeias were Othni, and Raphael, and Obed,
@c    Elizabad, and his brethren most valiant men:  and Eliu, and Samachias.

@c    26:8. All these of the sons of Obededom:  they, and their sons, and
@c    their brethren most able men for service, sixty-two of Obededom.

@c    26:9. And the sons of Meselemia, and their brethren strong men, were
@c    eighteen.

