@c    fit to be chief; and therefore he made Semri the chief.

@c    26:11. Helcias the second, Tabelias the third, Zacharias the fourth:
@c    all these the sons, and the brethren of Hosa, were thirteen.

@c    26:12. Among these were the divisions of the porters, so that the
@c    chiefs of the wards, as well as their brethren, always ministered in
@c    the house of the Lord.

@c    26:13. And they cast lots equally, both little and great, by their
@c    families for every one of the gates.

@c    26:14. And the lot of the east fell to Selemias.  But to his son
@c    Zacharias, a very wise and learned man, the north gate fell by lot.

@c    26:15. And to Obededom and his sons that towards the south:  in which
@c    part of the house was the council of the ancients.

@c    26:16. To Sephim, and Hosa towards the west, by the gate which leadeth
@c    to the way of the ascent:  ward against ward.

@c    26:17. Now towards the east were six Levites:  and towards the north
@c    four a day:  and towards the south likewise four a day:  and where the
