@c    26:27. Out of the wars, and the spoils won in battles, which they had
@c    consecrated to the building and furniture of the temple of the Lord.

@c    26:28. And all these things that Samuel the seer and Saul the son of
@c    Cis, and Abner the son of Ner, and Joab the son of Sarvia had
@c    sanctified:  and whosoever had sanctified those things, they were under
@c    the hand of Selemith and his brethren.

@c    26:29. But Chonenias and his sons were over the Isaarites, for the
@c    business abroad over Israel to teach them and judge them.

@c    26:30. And of the Hebronites Hasabias, and his brethren most able men,
@c    a thousand seven hundred had the charge over Israel beyond the Jordan
@c    westward, in all the works of the Lord, and for the service of the
@c    king.

@c    26:31. And the chief of the Hebronites was Jeria according to their
@c    families and kindreds.  In the fortieth year of the reign of David they
@c    were numbered, and there were found most valiant men in Jazer Galaad,

@c    26:32. And his brethren of stronger age, two thousand seven hundred
@c    chiefs of families.  And king David made them rulers over the Rubenites
@c    and the Gadites, and the half tribe of Manasses, for all the service of
@c    God, and the king.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 27


@c    The twelve captains for every month; the twelve princes of the tribes.
@c    David's several officers.

@c    27:1. Now the children of Israel according to their number, the heads
@c    of families, captains of thousands and of hundreds, and officers, that
@c    served the king according to their companies, who came in and went out
@c    every month in the year, under every chief were four and twenty
@c    thousand.

@c    27:2. Over the first company the first month Jesboam, the son of
@c    Zabdiel was chief, and under him were four and twenty thousand.

@c    27:3. Of the sons of Phares, the chief of all the captains in the host
@c    in the first month.

@c    27:4. The company of the second month was under Dudia, an Ahohite, and
@c    after him was another named Macelloth, who commanded a part of the army
@c    of four and twenty thousand.

@c    27:5. And the captain of the third company for the third month, was
@c    Banaias the son of Joiada the priest:  and in his division were four and
@c    twenty thousand.

@c    27:6. This is that Banaias the most valiant among the thirty, and above
@c    the thirty.  And Amizabad his son commanded his company.

@c    27:7. The fourth, for the fourth month, was Asahel the brother of Joab,
@c    and Zabadias his son after him:  and in his company were four and twenty
@c    thousand.

@c    27:8. The fifth captain for the fifth month, was Samaoth a Jezerite:
@c    and his company were four and twenty thousand.

@c    27:9. The sixth, for the sixth month, was Hira the son of Acces a
@c    Thecuite:  and in his company were four and twenty thousand.

@c    27:10. The seventh, for the seventh month, was Helles a Phallonite of
@c    the sons of Ephraim:  and in his company were four and twenty thousand.

@c    27:11. The eighth, for the eighth month, was Sobochai a Husathite of
@c    the race of Zarahi:  and in his company were four and twenty thousand.

@c    27:12. The ninth, for the ninth month, was Abiezer an Anathothite of
@c    the sons of Jemini, and in his company were four and twenty thousand.

@c    27:13. The tenth, for the tenth month, was Marai, who was a
@c    Netophathite of the race of Zarai:  and in his company were four and
@c    twenty thousand.

@c    27:14. The eleventh, for the eleventh month, was Banaias, a
@c    Pharathonite of the sons of Ephraim:  and in his company were four and
@c    twenty thousand.

@c    27:15. The twelfth, for the twelfth month, was Holdai a Netophathite,
@c    of the race of Gothoniel:  and in his company were four and twenty
@c    thousand.

@c    27:16. Now the chiefs over the tribes of Israel were these:  over the
@c    Rubenites, Eliezer the son of Zechri was ruler:  over the Simeonites,
@c    Saphatias the son of Maacha:

@c    27:17. Over the Levites, Hasabias the son of Camuel:  over the
@c    Aaronites, Sadoc:

@c    27:18. Over Juda, Eliu the brother of David over Issachar, Amri the son
@c    of Michael:

@c    27:19. Over the Zabulonites, Jesmaias the son of Adias:  over the
@c    Nephtalites, Jerimoth the son of Ozriel:

@c    27:20. Over the sons of Ephraim, Osee the son of Ozaziu:  over the half
@c    tribe of Manasses, Joel the son of Phadaia:

@c    27:21. And over the half tribe of Manasses in Galaad, Jaddo the son of
@c    Zacharias:  and over Benjamin, Jasiel the son of Abner.

@c    27:22. And over Dan, Ezrihel the son of Jeroham:  these were the princes
@c    of the children of Israel.

@c    27:23. But David would not number them from twenty years old and under:
@c    because the lord had said that he would multiply Israel like the stars
@c    of heaven.

@c    27:24. Joab the son of Sarvia began to number, but he finished not:
@c    because upon this there fell wrath upon Israel:  and therefore the
@c    number of them that were numbered, was not registered in the chronicles
@c    of king David.

@c    27:25. And over the king's treasures was Azmoth the son of Adiel:  and
@c    over those stores which were in the cities, and in the villages, and,
@c    in the castles, was Jonathan the son of Ozias.

@c    27:26. And over the tillage, and the husbandmen, who tilled the ground,
@c    was Ezri the son of Chelub:

@c    27:27. And over the dressers of the vine yards, was Semeias a
@c    Romathite:  and over the wine cellars, Zabdias an Aphonite.

@c    27:28. And over the oliveyards and the fig groves, which were in the
@c    plains, was Balanam a Gederite:  and over the oil cellars, Joas.

@c    27:29. And over the herds that fed in Saron, was Setrai a Saronite:  and
@c    over the oxen in the valleys, Saphat the son of Adli:

@c    27:30. And over the camels, Ubil an Ishmahelite and over the asses,
@c    Jadias a Meronathite:

@c    27:31. And over the sheep Jaziz an Agarene.  All these were the rulers
@c    of the substance of king David.

@c    27:32. And Jonathan David's uncle, a counsellor, a wise and learned
@c    man:  he and Jahiel the son of Hachamoni were with the king's sons.

@c    27:33. And Achitophel was the king's counsellor, and Chusai the
@c    Arachite, the king's friend.

@c    27:34. And after Achitophel was Joiada the son of Banaias, and
@c    Abiathar.  And the general of the king's army was Joab.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 28


@c    David's speech, in a solemn assembly:  his exhortation to Solomon.  He
@c    giveth him a pattern of the temple.

@c    28:1. And David assembled all the chief men of Israel, the princes of
@c    the tribes, and the captains of the companies, who waited on the king:
@c    and the captains over thousands, and over hundreds, and them who had
@c    the charge over the substance and possessions of the king, and his sons
@c    with the officers of the court, and the men of power, and all the
@c    bravest of the army at Jerusalem.

@c    28:2. And the king rising up, and standing said:  Hear me, my brethren
@c    and my people:  I had a thought to have built a house, in which the ark
@c    of the Lord, and the footstool of our God might rest:  and prepared all
@c    things for the building.

@c    28:3. And God said to me:  Thou shalt not build a house to my name:
@c    because thou art a man of war, and hast shed blood.

@c    28:4. But the Lord God of Israel chose me of all the house of my
@c    father, to be king over Israel for ever:  for of Juda he chose the
@c    princes:  and of the house of Juda, my father's house:  and among the
@c    sons of my father, it pleased him to choose me king over all Israel.

@c    28:5. And among my sons (for the Lord hath given me many sons) he hath
@c    chosen Solomon my son, to sit upon the throne of the kingdom of the
@c    Lord over Israel.

@c    28:6. And he said to me:  Solomon thy son shall build my house, and my
@c    courts:  for I have chosen him to be my son, and I will be a father to
@c    him.

@c    28:7. And I will establish his kingdom for ever, it he continue to keep
@c    my commandments, and my judgments, as at this day.

@c    28:8. Now then before all the assembly of Israel, in the hearing of our
@c    God, keep ye, and seek all the commandments of the Lord our God:  that
@c    you may possess the good land, and may leave it to your children after
@c    you for ever.

@c    28:9. And thou my son Solomon, know the God of thy father, and serve
@c    him with a perfect heart, and a willing mind:  for the Lord searcheth
@c    all hearts, and understandeth all the thoughts of minds.  If thou seek
@c    him, thou shalt find him:  but if thou forsake him, he will cast thee
@c    off for ever.

@c    28:10. Now therefore seeing the Lord hath chosen thee to build the
@c    house of the sanctuary, take courage, and do it.

@c    28:11. And David gave to Solomon his son a description of the porch,
@c    and of the temple, and of the treasures, and of the upper floor, and of
@c    the inner chambers, and of the house for the mercy seat,

@c    28:12. As also of all the courts, which he had in his thought, and of
@c    the chambers round about, for the treasures of the house of the Lord,
@c    and for the treasures of the consecrated things,

@c    28:13. And of the divisions of the priests and of the Levites, for all
@c    the works of the house of the Lord, and for all the vessels of the
@c    service of the temple of the Lord.

@c    28:14. Gold by weight for every vessel for the ministry.  And silver by
@c    weight according to the diversity of the vessels and uses.

@c    28:15. He gave also gold for the golden candlesticks, and their lamps,
@c    according to the dimensions of every candlestick, and the lamps
@c    thereof.  In like manner also he gave silver by weight for the silver
@c    candlesticks, and for their lamps according to the diversity of the
@c    dimensions of them.

@c    28:16. He gave also gold for the tables of proposition, according to
@c    the diversity of the tables:  in like manner also silver for other
@c    tables of silver.

@c    28:17. For fleshhooks also, and bowls, and censors of fine gold, and
@c    for little lions of gold, according to the measure he gave by weight,
@c    for every lion.  In like manner also for lions of silver he set aside a
@c    different weight of silver.

@c    28:18. And for the altar of incense, he gave the purest gold:  and to
@c    make the likeness of the chariot of the cherubims spreading their
@c    wings, and covering the ark of the covenant of the Lord.

@c    28:19. All these things, said he, came to me written by the hand of the
@c    Lord that I might understand all the works of the pattern.

@c    28:20. And David said to Solomon his son:  Act like a man, and take
@c    courage, and do:  fear not, and be not dismayed:  for the Lord my God
@c    will be with thee, and will not leave thee, nor forsake thee, till thou
@c    hast finished all the work for the service of the house of the Lord.

@c    28:21. Behold the courses of the priests and the Levites, for every
@c    ministry of the house of the Lord, stand by thee, and are ready, and
@c    both the princes, and the people know how to execute all thy
@c    commandments.



@c    1 Paralipomenon Chapter 29


@c    David by word and example encourageth the princes to contribute
@c    liberally to the building of the temple.  His thanksgiving, prayer, and
@c    sacrifices:  his death.

@c    29:1. And king David said to all the assembly:  Solomon my son, whom
@c    alone God hath chosen, is as yet young and tender:  and the work is
@c    great, for a house is prepared not for man, but for God.

@c    29:2. And I with all my ability have prepared the expenses for the
@c    house of my God.  Gold for vessels of gold, and silver for vessels of
@c    silver, brass for things of brass, iron for things of iron, wood for
@c    things of wood:  and onyx stones, and stones like alabaster, and of
@c    divers colours, and all manner of precious stones, and marble of Paros
@c    in great abundance.

@c    29:3. Now over and above the things which I have offered into the house
@c    of my God I give of my own proper goods, gold and silver for the temple
@c    of my God, beside what things I have prepared for the holy house.

@c    29:4. Three thousand talents of gold of the gold of Ophir:  and seven
@c    thousand talents of refined silver, to overlay the walls of the temple.

@c    29:5. And gold for wheresoever there is need of gold:  and silver for
@c    wheresoever there is need of silver, for the works to be made by the
@c    hands of the artificers:  now if any man is willing to offer, let him
@c    fill his hand to day, and offer what he pleaseth to the Lord.

@c    29:6. Then the heads of the families, and the princes of the tribes of
@c    Israel and the captains of thousands, and of hundreds, and the
@c    overseers of the king's possessions promised,

@c    29:7. And they gave for the works of the house of the Lord, of gold,
@c    five thousand talents, and ten thousand solids:  of silver ten thousand
@c    talents:  and of brass eighteen thousand talents:  and of iron a hundred
@c    thousand talents.

@c    29:8. And all they that had stones, gave them to the treasures of the
@c    house of the Lord, by the hand of Jahiel the Gersonite.

@c    29:9. And the people rejoiced, when they promised their offerings
@c    willingly:  because they offered them to the Lord with all their heart:
@c    and David the king rejoiced also with a great joy.

@c    29:10. And he blessed the Lord before all the multitude, and he said:
@c    Blessed art thou, O Lord the God of Israel, our father from eternity to
@c    eternity.

@c    29:11. Thine, O Lord, is magnificence, and power, and glory, and
@c    victory:  and to thee is praise:  for all that is in heaven, and in
@c    earth, is thine:  thine is the kingdom, O Lord, and thou art above all
@c    princes.

@c    29:12. Thine are riches, and thine is glory, thou hast dominion over
@c    all, in thy hand is power and might:  in thy hand greatness, and the
@c    empire of all things.

@c    29:13. Now therefore our God we give thanks to thee, and we praise thy
@c    glorious name.

@c    29:14. Who am I, and what is my people, that we should be able to
@c    promise thee all these things?  all things are thine:  and we have given
@c    thee what we received of thy hand.

@c    29:15. For we are sojourners before thee, and strangers, as were all
@c    our fathers.  I Our days upon earth are as a shadow, and there is no
@c    stay.

@c    29:16. O Lord our God, all this store that we have prepared to build
@c    thee a house for thy holy name, is from thy hand, and all things are
@c    thine.

@c    29:17. I know my God that thou provest hearts, and lovest simplicity,
@c    wherefore I also in the simplicity of my heart, have joyfully offered
@c    all these things:  and I have seen with great joy thy people, which are
@c    here present, offer thee their offerings.

@c    29:18. O Lord God of Abraham, and of Isaac, and of Israel our fathers,
@c    keep for ever this will of their heart, and let this mind remain always
@c    for the worship of thee.

@c    29:19. And give to Solomon my son a perfect heart, that he may keep thy
@c    commandments, thy testimonies, and thy ceremonies, and do all things:
@c    and build the house, for which I have provided the charges.

@c    29:20. And David commanded all the assembly:  Bless ye the Lord our God.
@c    And all the assembly blessed the Lord the God of their fathers:  and
@c    they bowed themselves and worshipped God, and then the king.

@c    29:21. And they sacrificed victims to the Lord:  and they offered
@c    holocausts the next day, a thousand bullocks, a thousand rams, a
@c    thousand lambs, with their libations, and with every thing prescribed
@c    most abundantly for all Israel.

@c    29:22. And they ate, and drank before the Lord that day with great joy.
@c    And they anointed the second time Solomon the son of David.  And they
@c    anointed him to the Lord to be prince, and Sadoc to be high priest.

@c    29:23. And Solomon sat on the throne of the Lord as king instead of
@c    David his father, and he pleased all:  and all Israel obeyed him.

@c    29:24. And all the princes, and men of power, and all the sons of king
@c    David gave their hand, and were subject to Solomon the king.

@c    29:25. And the Lord magnified Solomon over all Israel:  and gave him the
@c    glory of a reign, such as no king of Israel had before him.

@c    29:26. So David the son of Isai reigned over all Israel.

@c    29:27. And the days that he reigned over Israel, were forty years:  in
@c    Hebron he reigned seven years, and in Jerusalem three and thirty years.

@c    29:28. And he died in a good age, full of days, and riches, and glory.
@c    And Solomon his son reigned in his stead.

@c    29:29. Now the acts of king David first and last are written in the
@c    book of Samuel the seer, and in the book of Nathan the prophet, and in
@c    the book of Gad the seer:

@c    29:30. And of all his reign, and his valour, and of the times that
@c    passed under him, either in Israel, or in all the kingdoms of the
@c    countries.
